01:05:08,295 --> 01:05:09,644
[BOTH GRUNT]

1023
01:05:11,124 --> 01:05:12,343
[EXHALES]

1024
01:05:14,345 --> 01:05:16,390
[BOTH LAUGHING]

1025
01:05:26,923 --> 01:05:27,924
Good night.

1026
01:05:32,145 --> 01:05:33,364
Good night.

1027
01:05:41,285 --> 01:05:42,982
[SIGHS]

1028
01:05:43,026 --> 01:05:44,549
[WHISPERS] Good night, Bee.

1029
01:05:57,692 --> 01:06:01,044
Morning, buddy.
I got to go to work, okay?

1030
01:06:01,087 --> 01:06:05,004
Bee. Listen to me.
You need to stay
in this garage, okay?

1031
01:06:05,048 --> 01:06:06,179
After what
happened last night,

1032
01:06:06,223 --> 01:06:08,181
I'm pretty sure the cops
are looking for you,

1033
01:06:08,225 --> 01:06:10,967
and, uh, you don't
exactly blend in.

1034
01:06:12,055 --> 01:06:13,795
I'll be back, all right?

1035
01:06:13,839 --> 01:06:15,058
[BUMBLEBEE WHINES]

1036
01:06:17,321 --> 01:06:18,583
Here.

1037
01:06:20,585 --> 01:06:22,065
You can have my Pop-Tart.

1038
01:06:23,283 --> 01:06:25,416
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

1039
01:06:27,592 --> 01:06:30,421
♪ Take your baby by the hand

1040
01:06:31,813 --> 01:06:33,598
[SIZZLING]

1041
01:06:33,641 --> 01:06:37,776
I need you to go
to the frozen banana stand
and steal some sticks.

1042
01:06:38,951 --> 01:06:40,344
We're out of sticks.

1043
01:06:40,387 --> 01:06:42,737
Can't we just sell the
hot dogs without the sticks?

1044
01:06:43,216 --> 01:06:44,217
No.

1045
01:06:44,261 --> 01:06:45,305
[MUSIC PLAYING ON TV]

1046
01:06:45,349 --> 01:06:47,046
♪ Don't, don't, don't...

1047
01:06:47,090 --> 01:06:49,005
[BUMBLEBEE GRUNTING]

1048
01:06:49,048 --> 01:06:50,745
[CONAN WHINING]

1049
01:06:56,316 --> 01:06:58,014
[WHIMPERS]

1050
01:07:21,863 --> 01:07:23,213
[BIRD CHIRPING]

1051
01:07:54,592 --> 01:07:56,768
[GAS FIZZING]

1052
01:08:01,164 --> 01:08:02,513
[CLATTERING]

1053
01:08:12,262 --> 01:08:13,524
[CONAN BARKS]

1054
01:08:18,311 --> 01:08:19,747
[SOFA CREAKS]

1055
01:08:27,581 --> 01:08:29,627
[CLOCK TICKING]

1056
01:08:44,859 --> 01:08:45,947
[DINGS]

1057
01:08:47,079 --> 01:08:48,602
[MACHINE GURGLING]

1058
01:09:07,969 --> 01:09:09,319
[POWERING UP]

1059
01:09:19,416 --> 01:09:20,591
[BEEPING]

1060
01:09:23,420 --> 01:09:26,336
What's happening here?We got a hit, I think.
Where's that location?

1061
01:09:26,379 --> 01:09:29,991
Near San Francisco.
A coastal town
named Brighton Falls.

1062
01:09:41,046 --> 01:09:43,135
[EXPLOSION][DOG BARKING]

1063
01:09:45,398 --> 01:09:46,834
[EXPLOSION]

1064
01:09:48,619 --> 01:09:50,882
You have a personal call.

1065
01:09:55,191 --> 01:09:57,758
Hello? Charlie, hey, it's Memo.

1066
01:09:57,802 --> 01:10:00,065
You got to come home
right now.

1067
01:10:02,589 --> 01:10:04,112
[ENGINE REVVING]

1068
01:10:04,156 --> 01:10:05,636
[TIRES SCREECH]

1069
01:10:07,072 --> 01:10:09,727
It's bad.
It's really, really bad.

1070
01:10:12,295 --> 01:10:13,818
[CHARLIE GASPS]

1071
01:10:15,080 --> 01:10:16,299
Where's Bumblebee?

1072
01:10:22,130 --> 01:10:25,569
Bumblebee,
what have you done?

1073
01:10:25,612 --> 01:10:28,093
What were you thinking?
What...

1074
01:10:28,136 --> 01:10:30,791
I told you to hide
in the garage!

1075
01:10:32,576 --> 01:10:34,186
Great.

1076
01:10:34,230 --> 01:10:36,144
Helpful shame spiral, Bee.

1077
01:10:36,188 --> 01:10:37,798
[BUMBLEBEE WHINES]

1078
01:10:37,842 --> 01:10:41,498
I'm not mad, okay?
This is all my fault.

1079
01:10:41,541 --> 01:10:43,326
I never should
have left you.

1080
01:10:47,852 --> 01:10:49,941
MEMO: Hey, okay,
maybe don't transform
all the way?

1081
01:10:49,984 --> 01:10:52,291
We've still got
to get you through
the door.

1082
01:10:52,335 --> 01:10:53,553
[BUMBLEBEE GROANS]

1083
01:10:53,597 --> 01:10:55,033
Come on, buddy.

1084
01:10:56,077 --> 01:10:57,253
It's okay.

1085
01:11:06,479 --> 01:11:08,046
[SIGHS][OBJECTS CLATTERING]

1086
01:11:11,354 --> 01:11:13,269
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

1087
01:11:16,402 --> 01:11:17,969
I am so screwed.

1088
01:11:28,371 --> 01:11:30,024
[GRUNTING]

1089
01:11:31,199 --> 01:11:33,898
And now you're
crippled for life.

1090
01:11:33,941 --> 01:11:36,030
Honey, watch the hair.

1091
01:11:37,728 --> 01:11:39,295
[DOOR CLOSES][INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1092
01:11:41,688 --> 01:11:44,430
Go. Now. But be quiet.

1093
01:11:44,474 --> 01:11:45,953
Mom, wait!

1094
01:11:45,997 --> 01:11:47,172
[GASPS]

1095
01:11:48,260 --> 01:11:49,435
Oh, my God!

1096
01:11:51,307 --> 01:11:52,220
[GASPS]

1097
01:11:52,264 --> 01:11:54,048
Mom...SALLY: What happened?

1098
01:11:54,092 --> 01:11:56,268
CHARLIE: I'm sorry.
This is all my fault.

1099
01:11:56,312 --> 01:11:58,052
What'd you do to my TV?

1100
01:11:58,096 --> 01:12:01,317
Look, Mom, I can explain.
We will talk about this
later, all right?

1101
01:12:01,360 --> 01:12:03,580
Now, I have to go.Are you kidding me?

1102
01:12:03,623 --> 01:12:05,146
No. You're not
going anywhere.

1103
01:12:05,190 --> 01:12:07,801
It's about my car.
It's really important.About your car?

1104
01:12:07,845 --> 01:12:12,110
That you spend all day
and night shut in that garage,
doing God-knows-what with?

1105
01:12:12,153 --> 01:12:14,242
Mom, I can't.
I really can't right now.

1106
01:12:14,286 --> 01:12:16,636
Oh, no, you really can,
Charlie.

1107
01:12:16,680 --> 01:12:18,682
You really can.

1108
01:12:18,725 --> 01:12:19,944
I have had it!

1109
01:12:19,987 --> 01:12:22,381
Your attitude,
your always sulking around.

1110
01:12:22,425 --> 01:12:26,080
You brought home
that piece of crap
without even asking me!

1111
01:12:26,124 --> 01:12:29,083
Everyone in this family
is trying to be happy,

1112
01:12:29,127 --> 01:12:31,695
and all you want to do
is make things harder.

1113
01:12:31,738 --> 01:12:33,479
You know, Mom,
just because you've moved on

1114
01:12:33,523 --> 01:12:37,048
and you're happy with your
new life doesn't mean I have!

1115
01:12:37,091 --> 01:12:39,833
You've found a replacement
for my dad and I haven't,

1116
01:12:39,877 --> 01:12:40,965
okay, and I never will!

1117
01:12:41,008 --> 01:12:43,359
So I'm sorry if that
makes things harder,

1118
01:12:43,402 --> 01:12:45,099
but in ten months from now

1119
01:12:45,143 --> 01:12:47,058
you won't even have
to deal with me!

1120
01:12:48,799 --> 01:12:50,191
Charlie!

1121
01:12:51,671 --> 01:12:52,977
[SIGHS]

1122
01:13:00,201 --> 01:13:01,507
Hey, you okay?

1123
01:13:03,335 --> 01:13:04,380
Yeah.

1124
01:13:07,121 --> 01:13:09,123
I just feel like
ever since my dad died,

1125
01:13:09,167 --> 01:13:12,344
I've become this drain
on everyone, and I hate it.

1126
01:13:13,780 --> 01:13:15,129
It's like everybody expects me

1127
01:13:15,173 --> 01:13:17,262
to act like
nothing ever happened,

1128
01:13:17,305 --> 01:13:19,917
and it's impossible
to do that.

1129
01:13:22,049 --> 01:13:25,270
About your dad,
I'm really sorry.

1130
01:13:25,705 --> 01:13:27,664
Thanks.

1131
01:13:27,707 --> 01:13:30,493
You know, there's
this quote that I like.

1132
01:13:32,146 --> 01:13:35,541
"The darkest nights
produce the brightest stars."

1133
01:13:39,850 --> 01:13:41,373
That's nice.

1134
01:13:42,243 --> 01:13:44,202
My mom got it
from Weight Watchers.

1135
01:13:46,422 --> 01:13:47,553
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

1136
01:13:50,817 --> 01:13:52,036
[BRAKES SQUEAL]

1137
01:13:58,956 --> 01:14:01,611
Get out and move
away from the vehicle.

1138
01:14:01,654 --> 01:14:02,786
[ENGINE REVS]

1139
01:14:02,829 --> 01:14:04,614
Stay cool, Bee.

1140
01:14:04,657 --> 01:14:06,877
[REVS AND STOPS]

1141
01:14:13,753 --> 01:14:14,798
What's going on?

1142
01:14:14,841 --> 01:14:16,321
[MEMO GRUNTS]

1143
01:14:16,364 --> 01:14:17,191
Hey!

1144
01:14:17,235 --> 01:14:19,019
Come on!CHARLIE: Stop it!

1145
01:14:19,672 --> 01:14:21,282
Let go of me!

1146
01:14:21,326 --> 01:14:22,283
[SCREAMS]

1147
01:14:22,327 --> 01:14:24,503
Weapons now!
Take it down!Run!

1148
01:14:24,547 --> 01:14:26,418
No, don't run.
Do not run!

1149
01:14:26,462 --> 01:14:27,637
[CHARLIE GRUNTS]

1150
01:14:30,335 --> 01:14:31,379
She ran.

1151
01:14:31,423 --> 01:14:33,077
[CHARLIE SCREAMING]

1152
01:14:38,256 --> 01:14:39,431
[GRUNTS]

1153
01:14:41,564 --> 01:14:43,827
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

1154
01:14:43,870 --> 01:14:45,916
[ENGINE REVS][TIRES SCREECH]

1155
01:14:54,925 --> 01:14:56,492
Please tell me
they're on our side.

1156
01:15:02,585 --> 01:15:03,890
[GRUNTS]

1157
01:15:03,934 --> 01:15:05,457
[GROANS]

1158
01:15:09,548 --> 01:15:11,507
SHATTER: No more running.

1159
01:15:11,550 --> 01:15:13,552
No more hiding.

1160
01:15:13,596 --> 01:15:15,467
[VISOR TRILLING]

1161
01:15:17,164 --> 01:15:21,865
B-127, you're a traitor
and a coward.

1162
01:15:21,908 --> 01:15:24,302
Tell us where
Optimus Prime is hiding.

1163
01:15:27,348 --> 01:15:29,394
Bee, look out![DROPKICK GRUNTS]

1164
01:15:31,135 --> 01:15:33,093
DROPKICK:
Why isn't he fighting back?

1165
01:15:33,137 --> 01:15:34,921
[CHARLIE GRUNTS]DROPKICK:
Why don't you fight?

1166
01:15:34,965 --> 01:15:36,575
Leave him alone!
Please!

1167
01:15:40,623 --> 01:15:41,972
Again.

1168
01:15:42,015 --> 01:15:44,104
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING]

1169
01:15:45,410 --> 01:15:46,411
Hit it again!

1170
01:15:47,891 --> 01:15:49,457
Stop! Stop it!

1171
01:15:49,501 --> 01:15:51,416
[GRUNTS AND GROANS]

1172
01:16:04,647 --> 01:16:06,953
[BREATHING STEADILY]

1173
01:16:06,997 --> 01:16:09,303
[MUFFLED CONVERSATIONS]

1174
01:16:11,523 --> 01:16:13,003
[GROANS]

1175
01:16:19,879 --> 01:16:22,839
AGENT BURNS: Your daughter
stole government
property, Mrs. Watson.

1176
01:16:22,882 --> 01:16:25,145
SALLY: She's been
having trouble adjusting,

1177
01:16:25,189 --> 01:16:27,844
but we had no idea
it was this serious.

1178
01:16:27,887 --> 01:16:29,106
I...

1179
01:16:29,149 --> 01:16:30,629
Charlie. Honey.

1180
01:16:30,673 --> 01:16:33,632
I didn't steal anything,
and he doesn't belong to them.

1181
01:16:33,676 --> 01:16:35,068
"He?"AGENT BURNS: Ma'am.

1182
01:16:35,112 --> 01:16:37,505
I can assure you
that it is an "it".

1183
01:16:37,549 --> 01:16:39,638
And "it" is a highly dangerous
war machine.

1184
01:16:39,682 --> 01:16:42,946
No, he isn't, okay, Mom?
He's not some "war machine."

1185
01:16:42,989 --> 01:16:46,384
I don't know
what he is, but...

1186
01:16:46,427 --> 01:16:48,081
He's my friend.

1187
01:16:48,125 --> 01:16:50,954
Ma'am, your daughter's had
a traumatic experience today.

1188
01:16:50,997 --> 01:16:53,173
Maybe doesn't understand
everything she's seen.

1189
01:16:53,217 --> 01:16:54,479
She's disoriented.

1190
01:16:54,522 --> 01:16:57,134
No, I'm fine, Mom.
I'm completely fine, okay?

1191
01:16:57,177 --> 01:17:00,006
You have to
believe me, please.
I didn't steal anything!

1192
01:17:00,050 --> 01:17:02,400
Stop! Just go
to your room.

1193
01:17:02,966 --> 01:17:04,532
[SIGHS]

1194
01:17:09,407 --> 01:17:11,452
RON: When I was going
through puberty,

1195
01:17:12,715 --> 01:17:14,673
I stole things, too.

1196
01:17:14,717 --> 01:17:17,633
Stole a box
of Mallomars once.Yeah, we know.

1197
01:17:19,722 --> 01:17:21,245
[SIGHS]

1198
01:17:56,759 --> 01:17:58,325
[MOUTHING]

1199
01:18:01,198 --> 01:18:02,416
OTIS: Boom.

1200
01:18:03,461 --> 01:18:05,028
Caught you.

1201
01:18:05,071 --> 01:18:06,943
Oh, Mom's gonna love this.

1202
01:18:06,986 --> 01:18:08,727
Look, Otis, you need
to go home and...

1203
01:18:08,771 --> 01:18:10,250
Mom!

1204
01:18:10,294 --> 01:18:13,123
No, Otis, stop it!
Why would you do that?[GRUNTING]

1205
01:18:13,166 --> 01:18:15,865
Let go of me!
You're touching my buttocks![SHUSHES]

1206
01:18:15,908 --> 01:18:18,737
I will tell you a secret
if you shut up.

1207
01:18:19,956 --> 01:18:23,742
Okay, so, um,
this is my room.

1208
01:18:23,786 --> 01:18:25,439
Just make yourself at home.

1209
01:18:25,483 --> 01:18:27,572
These are actually
my sister's stuff.

1210
01:18:27,615 --> 01:18:30,531
She likes playing pranks, like
putting her stuff over here.

1211
01:18:30,575 --> 01:18:32,751
CHARLIE:
Can I, uh, sit down?Yeah, yeah. Mmm-hmm.

1212
01:18:32,795 --> 01:18:34,405
REPORTER: [ON TV]
Residents of Brighton Falls
have been witness

1213
01:18:34,448 --> 01:18:36,755
to an unusual sight
this evening.

1214
01:18:36,799 --> 01:18:40,280
Armed Forces pouring into town as part of what we are told

1215
01:18:40,324 --> 01:18:43,196
is a routine military exercise

1216
01:18:43,240 --> 01:18:45,938
setting up camp
at our own McKinnon Air Base.

1217
01:18:45,982 --> 01:18:49,202
If Bumblebee's still alive,
that's where they're
keeping him.

1218
01:18:49,246 --> 01:18:51,291
We have to go.
We have to try and save him.

1219
01:18:51,335 --> 01:18:53,250
Count me in. I'll take point.

1220
01:18:54,251 --> 01:18:55,861
No, you won't.Come on.

1221
01:18:55,905 --> 01:18:57,471
No, Otis.

1222
01:18:57,515 --> 01:18:59,735
But I can help.
Master Larry says I...I need someone here.

1223
01:18:59,778 --> 01:19:03,913
I need someone reliable
to make sure that Mom and Ron
don't know that I'm gone.

1224
01:19:03,956 --> 01:19:05,479
I'm someone reliable.

1225
01:19:07,177 --> 01:19:08,569
Hell, yeah, you are.

1226
01:19:13,531 --> 01:19:14,706
Good luck.

1227
01:19:15,228 --> 01:19:16,795
You, too.

1228
01:19:16,839 --> 01:19:18,318
Get over here.

1229
01:19:18,841 --> 01:19:20,190
[CHARLIE SIGHING]

1230
01:19:23,149 --> 01:19:24,498
Oh.

1231
01:19:24,542 --> 01:19:25,717
Let's do this.

1232
01:19:28,241 --> 01:19:29,329
SHATTER: Tell us where

1233
01:19:29,373 --> 01:19:31,288
Optimus Prime
and the rebels are hiding,

1234
01:19:31,331 --> 01:19:34,291
and we can end this war.

1235
01:19:36,554 --> 01:19:37,598
Talk!

1236
01:19:37,642 --> 01:19:39,600
DR. POWELL:
Who is Optimus Prime?

1237
01:19:39,644 --> 01:19:42,212
SHATTER: This doesn't
concern you,
human Powell.

1238
01:19:42,603 --> 01:19:44,736
Last chance.

1239
01:19:45,084 --> 01:19:46,303
[METAL CLANGS]

1240
01:19:51,047 --> 01:19:53,658
MEMO: Are you sure
this is a good idea?

1241
01:19:53,701 --> 01:19:55,747
CHARLIE: It's a terrible idea,
but I've got to try it.

1242
01:19:55,791 --> 01:19:58,445
MEMO: You can't get...
Well, why don't you...
Stop, stop, wait...

1243
01:19:58,489 --> 01:20:01,579
How'd you know
the power was off?CHARLIE: I didn't. Let's go.

1244
01:20:07,150 --> 01:20:08,368
DROPKICK: Can I?

1245
01:20:08,412 --> 01:20:10,718
SHATTER:
His memory cells are fried.

1246
01:20:11,589 --> 01:20:12,808
Finish him.

1247
01:20:12,851 --> 01:20:14,244
[DROPKICK GRUNTS]

1248
01:20:19,075 --> 01:20:24,210
OPTIMUS: We will fight on.
Regroup, rebuild,
and retake our home.

1249
01:20:24,254 --> 01:20:26,865
But we must find refuge first.

1250
01:20:26,909 --> 01:20:28,432
You will travel to Earth.

1251
01:20:28,475 --> 01:20:31,130
Once we've gathered the others, we'll join you.

1252
01:20:31,174 --> 01:20:33,350
You must protect the planet.

1253
01:20:33,393 --> 01:20:38,877
If the Decepticons
find it, then our people
are truly finished.

1254
01:20:38,921 --> 01:20:41,184
Stay safe, soldier.

1255
01:20:41,227 --> 01:20:43,621
I am coming.

1256
01:20:45,275 --> 01:20:47,886
Prime is coming here?

1257
01:20:47,930 --> 01:20:50,062
They're all coming here.

1258
01:20:50,106 --> 01:20:54,327
This is our chance
to wipe out the Autobot
resistance for good.

1259
01:20:54,371 --> 01:20:57,896
We'll burn the whole
planet to cinders.

1260
01:20:57,940 --> 01:21:00,377
SHATTER: We must get word
to Cybertron immediately.

